HEADWORD: Myzostomata
<hw>My`zo*stom"a*ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>my`zein</grk> to suck + <grk>sto`ma</grk>,
<grk>-atos</grk>, mouth.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of
curious parasitic worms found on crinoids. The body is short and
disklike, with four pairs of suckers and five pairs of hook-bearing
parapodia on the under side.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

